 <div id="resc" class='box'><center><u>Previous Research:</u><br>
 As part of the LIGO SURF program 2021, I worked on improving the search methods for finding <b>gravitationally lensed gravitational waves</b>, where the curvature of spacetime can create multiple images of gravitational waves from the most energetic events in the universe. The lensing can hide some of these signals behind the noisy data, and no credible lensed events have been found yet! I imposed a condition to constrain the search to the sky location of a super-threshold event, as the images will come from approximately the same place in the sky. The improvements are still under testing.<br>
 I have also looked at exoplanet transits and indentifying planetary mass objects using photometric analysis and other methods; dynamical formation of planetary systems with tides using n-body code motivated by the anomoly of all the observed hot jupiters; and currently doing a masters project on AGN variability!
<br>
</div>

